Notes 2/17/17
Special Programming
Burris

pass by value
	changes copy of value
pass by reference
	passes address
	changes value of actual variable in memory

C pass by reference
	void fnc(*p1){ *p1 = 1; }
	fnc(&someval);
C++ pass by reference
	void fnc(&p1){p1 = 1;}
	fnc(someval);

Scope
	always uses local variables before global vars